Package: eyeScrollR
Type: Package
Title: Correctly place eye-tracking fixation data on areas of scrollable websites
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(person("Nathanael", "Larigaldie", email="larigaldie.n@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Anna", "Dreneva", role=c("aut")),
    person("Jacob", "Orquin", role=c("aut")))
Maintainer: Nathanael Larigaldie <larigaldie.n@gmail.com>
Description: Eye-tracking software usually outputs fixation coordinates from
    participants on the screen, but scrollable settings often require manual
    coordinate corrections from experimenters. This package allows for easier
    and mostly automatic corrections to use eye-tracking on scrollable websites,
    and generate fixation heatmaps on complete images taken from them, while
    managing potential immovable and/or retractable areas (e.g. navbars).
